.TH SORTIE 1 "March 2026" "sortie dev" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sortie \- intelligent file dispatcher
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sortie
.RI [ command ]
.RI [ flags ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sortie
is a rule\-based file automation tool that watches directories (like ~/Downloads
and ~/Desktop) and automatically dispatches files based on configurable rules.
Actions include moving, copying, renaming, compressing, extracting, running shell
commands, converting media, encrypting, uploading to cloud storage, and more.
.PP
Configuration uses a hybrid approach: a central config file at
.I ~/.config/sortie/config.yaml
defines watched directories and global rules, while optional per\-directory
.I .sortie.yaml
files add or override rules for specific directories. Per\-directory rules
take precedence over global rules (first\-match\-wins evaluation).
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B scan \fR[\fIdirectory...\fR]
Scan one or more directories (or all configured directories) and apply matching
rules. Use \fB\-\-dry\-run\fR to preview without executing.
.TP
.B watch
Watch all configured directories for new files in real time. Runs as a
foreground daemon with configurable debounce. Monitors its own binary and
exits gracefully when a new version is deployed. Exits cleanly on
SIGINT/SIGTERM.
.TP
.B history
Show recent dispatch actions. Use \fB\-n\fR or \fB\-\-limit\fR to control output.
.TP
.B undo \fR[\fIid\fR]
Reverse the most recent action, or a specific action by ID. Use \fB\-\-last N\fR
to undo the last N actions.
.TP
.B rules
List all configured rules (global and per\-directory).
.TP
.B rules test \fR\fIfile\fR
Show which rule would match a given file.
.TP
.B config
Show the resolved configuration.
.TP
.B config init
Create a starter config file with commented examples.
.TP
.B config path
Print the config file path.
.TP
.B status
Check if the watcher daemon is running, show watched directories and rule counts.
.TP
.B trash
List files in the trash directory.
.TP
.B trash purge
Permanently delete all files in trash.
.TP
.B man
Display this manual page.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-config " " \fIpath\fR
Config file path. Default: \fI~/.config/sortie/config.yaml\fR.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose output.
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show version information.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help.
.SS "scan flags"
.TP
.BR \-\-dry\-run
Preview actions without executing.
.SS "watch flags"
.TP
.BR \-\-dry\-run
Log what would happen without executing.
.TP
.BR \-\-debounce " " \fIduration\fR
Debounce period for file events. Default: 500ms.
.SS "history flags"
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-limit " " \fIN\fR
Maximum number of records to show. Default: 20.
.SS "undo flags"
.TP
.BR \-\-last " " \fIN\fR
Number of recent actions to undo. Default: 1.
.SH CONFIGURATION
.SS "Central Config"
Located at \fI~/.config/sortie/config.yaml\fR. Run \fBsortie config init\fR to
generate a starter file.
.PP
.nf
directories:
  \- path: ~/Downloads
    recursive: false

rules:
  \- name: images\-to\-photos
    match:
      extensions: [.jpg, .jpeg, .png, .heic]
    action:
      type: move
      dest: ~/Pictures/Sorted/{{.Year}}/{{.Month}}
.fi
.SS "Per\-Directory Config"
Place a \fI.sortie.yaml\fR file in any watched directory. These rules are
evaluated before global rules for that directory.
.PP
.nf
rules:
  \- name: pdfs\-to\-documents
    match:
      extensions: [.pdf]
    action:
      type: move
      dest: ~/Documents/PDFs
.fi
.SS "Match Conditions"
All specified conditions use AND logic.
.TP
.B extensions
List of file extensions (e.g., [.jpg, .png]).
.TP
.B glob
Filename glob pattern (e.g., "Screenshot*").
.TP
.B regex
Regular expression matched against filename.
.TP
.B min_size\fR, \fBmax_size
File size thresholds (e.g., "500MB", "1GB").
.TP
.B min_age\fR, \fBmax_age
File age thresholds (e.g., "30d", "2h").
.TP
.B mime_type
MIME type prefix match (e.g., "image/", "application/pdf").
.SS "Action Types"
.TP
.B move
Move the file to the destination.
.TP
.B copy
Copy the file to the destination.
.TP
.B rename
Rename the file using a template.
.TP
.B delete
Move the file to the trash directory (~/.config/sortie/trash/).
.TP
.B compress
Gzip the file and remove the original.
.TP
.B extract
Extract an archive (.zip, .tar, .tar.gz, .tar.bz2, .tar.xz) into the destination
directory. Supports zip via Go stdlib and tar variants via stdlib or \fBtar\fR(1).
.TP
.B symlink
Create a symbolic link at the destination pointing to the original file. The
source file is preserved.
.TP
.B chmod
Change file permissions. Requires the \fBmode\fR field (e.g., "0755"). Undoable \(em
the original permissions are restored.
.TP
.B checksum
Compute a hash of the file and write a sidecar (e.g., \fIfile.sha256\fR). Supports
\fBalgorithm\fR: "sha256" (default), "md5", "sha1". Optional \fBdest\fR overrides
sidecar path.
.TP
.B exec
Run an arbitrary shell command. The \fBcommand\fR field is template\-expanded (supports
\fB{{.Path}}\fR for full file path). Not undoable.
.TP
.B notify
Send a desktop notification (macOS via \fBosascript\fR) or webhook. If \fBmessage\fR
starts with http:// or https://, an HTTP POST with file metadata is sent. Requires
\fBtitle\fR and \fBmessage\fR fields. Not undoable.
.TP
.B convert
Run an external converter tool. Requires \fBtool\fR (e.g., "ffmpeg", "convert",
"pandoc") and \fBargs\fR (template\-expanded arguments). Source file is preserved.
Use \fB{{.Dest}}\fR in args to reference the output path.
.TP
.B resize
Resize an image. Default tool is \fBsips\fR (macOS). Supports \fBwidth\fR,
\fBheight\fR, and \fBpercentage\fR fields. Set \fBtool\fR to "convert" for
ImageMagick. Source file is preserved.
.TP
.B watermark
Stamp an image with an overlay using ImageMagick \fBcomposite\fR. Requires
\fBoverlay\fR (path to watermark image). Optional \fBgravity\fR (default: "center").
Source file is preserved.
.TP
.B ocr
Extract text from images/PDFs using \fBtesseract\fR. Optional \fBlanguage\fR
(default: "eng"). Output is a .txt sidecar file.
.TP
.B encrypt
Encrypt a file using \fBage\fR (default) or \fBgpg\fR. Requires \fBrecipient\fR.
Source file is preserved.
.TP
.B decrypt
Decrypt a file using \fBage\fR (default) or \fBgpg\fR. Optional \fBkey\fR for
key file path. Source file is preserved.
.TP
.B upload
Upload a file to cloud storage. Auto\-detects tool from URI scheme: s3:// uses
\fBaws\fR, gs:// uses \fBgsutil\fR. Requires \fBremote\fR field (template\-expanded).
Not undoable.
.TP
.B tag
Apply macOS Finder tags to a file via \fBxattr\fR. Requires \fBtags\fR list.
Not undoable.
.SS "Template Variables"
Destination paths and action fields support Go template syntax:
.TP
.B {{.Name}}
Filename without extension.
.TP
.B {{.Ext}}
Extension including dot.
.TP
.B {{.Path}}
Full source file path.
.TP
.B {{.Year}}\fR, \fB{{.Month}}\fR, \fB{{.Day}}
From file modification time.
.TP
.B {{.Date}}
YYYY\-MM\-DD format.
.TP
.B {{.Time}}
HH\-MM\-SS format.
.SS "Action Configuration Fields"
The following fields are available in the \fBaction:\fR block depending on
the action type:
.TP
.B dest
Destination path (template\-expanded). Used by move, copy, rename, compress,
extract, symlink, checksum, convert, resize, watermark, ocr, encrypt, decrypt.
.TP
.B mode
Permission string in octal (e.g., "0755"). Used by chmod.
.TP
.B algorithm
Hash algorithm: "sha256" (default), "md5", or "sha1". Used by checksum.
.TP
.B command
Shell command (template\-expanded, supports \fB{{.Path}}\fR). Used by exec.
.TP
.B title\fR, \fBmessage
Notification title and body (template\-expanded). Used by notify.
.TP
.B tool
External binary name. Used by convert (required), resize (default: "sips"),
watermark (default: "composite"), ocr (default: "tesseract"), encrypt/decrypt
(default: "age"), upload (auto\-detected from URI scheme).
.TP
.B args
Extra arguments (template\-expanded). Used by convert. Use \fB{{.Dest}}\fR and
\fB{{.Path}}\fR in the args string.
.TP
.B width\fR, \fBheight\fR, \fBpercentage
Image dimensions for resize. Specify width, height, or percentage.
.TP
.B overlay\fR, \fBgravity
Watermark overlay image path and placement (default: "center"). Common gravity
values: center, north, south, east, west, northeast, northwest, southeast,
southwest.
.TP
.B language
Tesseract language code (default: "eng"). Used by ocr.
.TP
.B recipient
Public key or key ID. Used by encrypt (required). For age: "age1...". For gpg:
email or key ID.
.TP
.B key
Key file path. Used by decrypt. For age: identity file. For gpg: keyring file.
.TP
.B tags
List of macOS Finder tag names (e.g., [Red, Finance]). Used by tag.
.TP
.B remote
Upload destination URI (template\-expanded). Used by upload. Supported schemes:
s3:// (uses \fBaws\fR), gs:// (uses \fBgsutil\fR).
.SS "External Tool Requirements"
Some actions require external tools to be installed:
.TP
.B resize
sips (built\-in on macOS) or ImageMagick convert.
.TP
.B watermark
ImageMagick composite. Install: \fBbrew install imagemagick\fR.
.TP
.B convert
User\-specified tool (e.g., ffmpeg, pandoc). Install as needed.
.TP
.B ocr
tesseract. Install: \fBbrew install tesseract\fR.
.TP
.B encrypt\fR, \fBdecrypt
age (default) or gpg. Install: \fBbrew install age\fR.
.TP
.B upload
aws CLI (for s3://) or gsutil (for gs://). Install: \fBbrew install awscli\fR.
.TP
.B tag
xattr (built\-in on macOS).
.TP
.B notify
osascript (built\-in on macOS) or HTTP webhook (no tool needed).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/sortie/config.yaml
Central configuration file.
.TP
.I ~/.config/sortie/history.json
Action history (JSON Lines format).
.TP
.I ~/.config/sortie/trash/
Trash directory for deleted files.
.TP
.I ~/.config/sortie/logs/
Log directory for watch mode.
.TP
.I ~/.config/sortie/sortie.pid
PID file written by the watcher daemon.
.TP
.I .sortie.yaml
Per\-directory rule overrides.
.SH EXAMPLES
Initialize configuration:
.PP
.nf
$ sortie config init
.fi
.PP
Preview what would happen in ~/Downloads:
.PP
.nf
$ sortie scan ~/Downloads \-\-dry\-run
.fi
.PP
Run the scan for real:
.PP
.nf
$ sortie scan
.fi
.PP
Start watching in real time:
.PP
.nf
$ sortie watch
.fi
.PP
Check which rule matches a file:
.PP
.nf
$ sortie rules test ~/Downloads/report.pdf
.fi
.PP
Undo the last 3 actions:
.PP
.nf
$ sortie undo \-\-last 3
.fi
.PP
Example rule using exec to strip EXIF data:
.PP
.nf
rules:
  \- name: strip\-exif
    match:
      extensions: [.jpg, .jpeg]
    action:
      type: exec
      command: "exiftool \-all= '{{.Path}}'"
.fi
.PP
Example rule to extract archives:
.PP
.nf
rules:
  \- name: extract\-archives
    match:
      extensions: [.zip, .tar.gz, .tgz]
    action:
      type: extract
      dest: ~/Downloads/Extracted/{{.Name}}
.fi
.PP
Example rule to encrypt sensitive files:
.PP
.nf
rules:
  \- name: encrypt\-sensitive
    match:
      glob: "confidential\-*"
    action:
      type: encrypt
      recipient: "age1..."
      dest: ~/Encrypted/{{.Name}}{{.Ext}}.age
.fi
.PP
Example rule to upload to S3:
.PP
.nf
rules:
  \- name: backup\-to\-s3
    match:
      extensions: [.pdf]
    action:
      type: upload
      remote: "s3://my\-bucket/docs/{{.Year}}/{{.Name}}{{.Ext}}"
.fi
.PP
Create symlinks for config files:
.PP
.nf
rules:
  \- name: symlink\-configs
    match:
      glob: "*.conf"
    action:
      type: symlink
      dest: ~/configs/{{.Name}}{{.Ext}}
.fi
.PP
Hash large downloads:
.PP
.nf
rules:
  \- name: hash\-downloads
    match:
      min_size: 100MB
    action:
      type: checksum
      algorithm: sha256
.fi
.PP
Resize images using sips:
.PP
.nf
rules:
  \- name: resize\-photos
    match:
      extensions: [.jpg, .png]
      min_size: 5MB
    action:
      type: resize
      width: 1920
      dest: ~/Pictures/Resized/{{.Name}}{{.Ext}}
.fi
.PP
Convert video with ffmpeg:
.PP
.nf
rules:
  \- name: convert\-videos
    match:
      extensions: [.mov, .avi]
    action:
      type: convert
      tool: ffmpeg
      args: "\-i {{.Path}} \-c:v libx264 {{.Dest}}"
      dest: ~/Videos/Converted/{{.Name}}.mp4
.fi
.PP
Watermark photos:
.PP
.nf
rules:
  \- name: watermark\-photos
    match:
      extensions: [.jpg, .png]
    action:
      type: watermark
      overlay: ~/watermark.png
      gravity: southeast
      dest: ~/Pictures/Watermarked/{{.Name}}{{.Ext}}
.fi
.PP
OCR scanned documents:
.PP
.nf
rules:
  \- name: ocr\-scans
    match:
      extensions: [.png, .tiff]
    action:
      type: ocr
      language: eng
      dest: ~/Documents/OCR/{{.Name}}.txt
.fi
.PP
Decrypt age\-encrypted files:
.PP
.nf
rules:
  \- name: decrypt\-incoming
    match:
      extensions: [.age]
    action:
      type: decrypt
      key: ~/.age/key.txt
      dest: ~/Decrypted/{{.Name}}
.fi
.PP
Send a desktop notification when a PDF arrives:
.PP
.nf
rules:
  \- name: new\-pdf\-alert
    match:
      extensions: [.pdf]
    action:
      type: notify
      title: "New PDF"
      message: "{{.Name}}{{.Ext}} arrived in Downloads"
.fi
.PP
Post to a webhook when a large file appears:
.PP
.nf
rules:
  \- name: large\-file\-webhook
    match:
      min_size: 1GB
    action:
      type: notify
      title: "Large file"
      message: "https://hooks.example.com/files"
.fi
.PP
Make shell scripts executable:
.PP
.nf
rules:
  \- name: make\-scripts\-executable
    match:
      extensions: [.sh]
    action:
      type: chmod
      mode: "0755"
.fi
.PP
Tag PDF receipts in Finder:
.PP
.nf
rules:
  \- name: tag\-receipts
    match:
      regex: "(?i)receipt"
      extensions: [.pdf]
    action:
      type: tag
      tags: [Green, Finance]
.fi
.PP
Compress old log files:
.PP
.nf
rules:
  \- name: compress\-logs
    match:
      extensions: [.log]
      min_age: 7d
    action:
      type: compress
      dest: ~/Archives/{{.Name}}{{.Ext}}.gz
.fi
.PP
Copy invoices to a shared folder:
.PP
.nf
rules:
  \- name: share\-invoices
    match:
      glob: "invoice\-*"
      extensions: [.pdf]
    action:
      type: copy
      dest: ~/Shared/Invoices/{{.Name}}{{.Ext}}
.fi
.PP
Rename screenshots with a date prefix:
.PP
.nf
rules:
  \- name: rename\-screenshots
    match:
      glob: "Screenshot*"
    action:
      type: rename
      dest: {{.Date}}_{{.Name}}{{.Ext}}
.fi
.PP
Delete temporary files older than 30 days:
.PP
.nf
rules:
  \- name: cleanup\-temp
    match:
      extensions: [.tmp, .bak]
      min_age: 30d
    action:
      type: delete
.fi
.SH RUNNING AS A SERVICE
On macOS, sortie can run as a launchd user agent to watch directories
automatically at login.
.PP
Install the service:
.PP
.nf
$ make install\-launchd
.fi
.PP
This creates a plist at
.I ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.msjurset.sortie.plist
that starts
.B sortie watch
at login. Logs go to
.IR ~/.config/sortie/logs/sortie.log .
.PP
The watch command monitors its own binary for changes. When you run
.B make deploy\fR,
the daemon detects the updated binary, exits gracefully, and launchd's
.B KeepAlive
automatically relaunches with the new version. No manual restart is needed
after deploying a new build.
.PP
Manage the service:
.PP
.nf
# Deploy (daemon auto\-restarts when it detects the new binary)
$ make deploy

# Manual stop
$ launchctl unload ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.msjurset.sortie.plist

# Manual start
$ launchctl load ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.msjurset.sortie.plist

# Restart after config changes (binary unchanged, manual reload needed)
$ launchctl unload ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.msjurset.sortie.plist
$ launchctl load ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.msjurset.sortie.plist

# Uninstall
$ make uninstall\-launchd
.fi
